org.gvsig.vectorediting.lib.api

Interface EditingService

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Observable, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DefaultEditingService

    public interface EditingService
extends Service, Observable
    This service is used to interact with Editing providers. Each instance of this has linked an Editing provider. At this moment services delegate all functionality to providers. To get an instance of this use EditingManager#getEditingService(String, org.gvsig.fmap.dal.feature.FeatureStore)

    • Method Detail

      • getDrawingStatus

        DrawingStatus getDrawingStatus(Point mousePosition)
                        throws DrawServiceException
        Gets state of drawing. If this service has sufficient values with mouse position to create geometries returns a DrawingStatus. List of geometries of drawing status object can be different from final geometries. Use this method to get a draft status information while user is drawing.
        Parameters:
        mousePosition - Mouse position to draw geometries.
        Returns:
        A DrawingStatus object with a list of geometries and information.
        Throws:
        DrawServiceException - if there are some error creating geometries.

      • getParameters

        java.util.List<EditingServiceParameter> getParameters()
        Gets a List with all parameters of service. Each parameter has name, description and types. See EditingServiceParameter.
        Returns:
        A list of EditingServiceParameter objects.

      • next

        EditingServiceParameter next()
        Gets next parameter needed by service. The parameter has information about its name, description and types. Returns null if all parameters have values.
        Returns:
        An EditingServiceParameter object that represents the next parameter.

      • stop

        void stop()
   throws StopServiceException
        Stops service. Use this method to stop and clean values of service.
        Throws:
        StopServiceException - Stops service initializing necessary parameters of service. This method is called when user cancels service.

      • finish

        Geometry finish()
         throws FinishServiceException
        Finalizes service. Use this method to get the result of service without store it to FeatureStore. Make sure that service has all required values.
        Returns:
        Geometry created or modified from added values.
        Throws:
        FinishServiceException - if there are some error getting values, creating geometries.

      • finishAndStore

        void finishAndStore()
             throws FinishServiceException
        Finalizes service and stores the result to FeatureStore of this service. Use this method to store the result of this service. Make sure that service has all required values.
        Throws:
        FinishServiceException - if there are some error getting values, creating geometries or inserting/updating/removing geometries from feature store.

      • start

        void start()
    throws StartServiceException,
           InvalidEntryException
        Starts service. Use this method before add values.
        Throws:
        StartServiceException - if there are some error starting service.
        InvalidEntryException - if the entry of provider is not valid
